==English==
===Etymology===
Variant of [[trist]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/trɪst/}}
*{{audio|en-us-tryst.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# ''(obsolete)'' A mutual agreement, a [[covenant]].
# A prearranged [[meeting]] or [[assignation]], now especially between [[lovers]] to meet at a specific place and time.

====Translations====
{{top}}
*[[Kurdish]]: {{trad|ku|jivan}} {{f}}
*Japanese: [[逢い引き]]（あいびき, aibiki）
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# ''(intransitive)'' To make a tryst; to agree to meet at a place.
# ''(transitive)'' To [[arrange]] or [[appoint]] (a meeting time etc.).
# ''(intransitive)'' To keep a tryst, to meet at an agreed place and time.

====Translations====
{{top}}
*[[Kurdish]]: (''intransitive'':) {{trad|ku|jivîn}}, [[çûn]] / [[hatin]] [[jivan]]ê, [[jivan]] kirin; {''transitive'':) {{trad|ku|jivandin}}
{{bottom}}

